  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The researchers want to investigate how fluid intake influences the symptoms of OAB. The
      researchers will recruit 45 patients with OAB and randomize them (blind) in 3 groups
      (low/normal/high fluid intake). Patients will follow this drink pattern for 2-5 days, while
      filling in an standard micturation diary for 2 days. This micturation diary is coupled to:
      collection of multiple urine samples, urine pH measurements, and a Perception of Intensity of
      Urgency Scale (PPIUS) scoring table. All this is collected by the patients themselves. Urine
      samples will be analysed for osmolality by the clinical chemistry department.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
